OSKIDO has gone back to school. The Kalawa Jazmee Records co-founder and director recently announced on social media that he would be studying a five-month project management course at the University of Pretoria. Fans praised Oskido for going back to study at the age of 54, despite already being successful. He told Daily Sun: “As a person, I have always believed in putting myself in a position to gain knowledge. The music business is changing so rapidly that to stay ahead, one has to keep learning of better ways to run a business.” Oskido said he chose to study project management because he wanted to implement the skills he learnt when running his businesses. “I chose this to gain the right mix of skills I need for the next part of my journey as an entrepreneur,” he said. ALSO READ |LERATO MVELASE GOES BACK TO SCHOOL In his posts on social media platforms, he advised people to keep growing and empowering themselves. He said he believed this was important for everyone, especially for the old. “I encourage people to always look at ways they can improve themselves through education,” he said. Oskido said more than anything else, he wanted to enjoy his journey. “I want to be stimulated and challenged while gaining knowledge on project management, risk management and financial aspects of projects. “I also hope to grow as a person,” he said.